snippet: At Facebook, ground zero for the nouveau tech riche in Silicon Valley, peer pressure dictates that consumption be kept on the down low.
abstract: Peer pressure at Facebook in Menlo Park, Calif, ground zero for the nouveau tech riche in Silicon Valley, dictates that consumption be kept on the down low; lucrative salaries and stock options are dangled to recruit or hold onto engineers, but the tech elite display an ambivalent, sometimes contradictory approach to wealth; money is treated as a measuring stick, gauging the power of the companies that entrepreneurs have built, rather than something to display.

snippet: The tech giant will refocus on product development and sales, executives say, and operations in China will most likely be spared.
abstract: Hewlett-Packard's chief executive Meg Whitman plans to cut 30,000 or more jobs from their 324,000-person work force; her goal is to refocus on increasing the efficiency of the company's sales force and on product development; operations in China, one of HP's highest growth areas, will most likely be spared.
